message: Join Congressman Lou Correa and Immigration legal experts for an informative Town Hall on Wednesday, April 19 at 6:00 pm at Carr Intermediate School Auditorium - 2120 W Edinger Ave, Santa Ana, CA 92704.  This is a free event, and everyone is welcome. Free parking is avaible.   Topic covered will include a DACA Legislative Update from Congressman Correa, several presentations by legal experts, and a Q&A session.  ---  Acompañen al Congresista Lou Correa y a expertos de inmigración para una sesión informativa.  El evento es gratuito y está abierto al público. Hay estacionamiento gratuito disponible.   Los temas que serán discutidos incluyen el programa de DACA y desarrollo de proyectos de ley por el Congresista Correa, varios expertos de leyes, acompañado por una sesión de preguntas.

Proud to stand with my fellow Congressional Hispanic Caucus members.
For my first appearance on the Floor, I thought I’d read the Constitution.

I am appalled by the terrorist attack in Jerusalem. Our thoughts and prayers are with the victims and their families. As Israel’s strongest ally, we must continue to work together to defeat the terrorists intent on destroying both of our nations.

As National Law Enforcement Apperception Day comes to a close let us take a moment to remember the law enforcement officers who protect us everyday. Thank you to all our law enforcement officers and their families.
Proud to join my fellow CHCI members in congratulating our new Chair Congressman Joaquin Castro!

For nearly 40 years, the Congressional Hispanic Caucus Institute has connected young Latinos with opportunities to become leaders to better their communities and their country. CHCI has empowered generations of Latinos to seek leadership. I am honored to be a member of CHCI and help future generations succeed.
We must defend the ACA and protect healthcare for 30 million Americans.
Today I had the opportunity to speak on the house floor and urge my colleagues to save Affordable Care Act. We need the ACA to protect access to healthcare for all Americans.

On Saturday I joined Rep. Judy Chu and Rep. Pete Aguilar in supporting immigrants and their allies. As many as 300,000 of the 2.5 million undocumented immigrants in California call Orange County home. They are a contributing part of our communities and economy, and need a way out of the shadows.
Today I joined fellow Southern California Representatives in defending the Affordable Care Act, and the great things it has done for middle class and working Americans. Watch it here.
As today comes to a close, let's take a moment to imagine how Dr. King would confront the challenges we will face in the coming year. We must not forget only love can overcome hate.
Watch me tomorrow on Today In LA at 6:45am on NBC LA.
Thank you Mayor Tom Tait for the visit. I look forward to continue making Anaheim a great place to live and work.

I have received much communication regarding tomorrow's Presidential inauguration, expressing opinions across the political spectrum. Clearly, while the election is over, the negativity continues. And, our Nation continues to be deeply divided.   We have a new President. Yet, the presidency is about our nation and our constitution, and not about an individual. This inauguration is another event in a line of peaceful transitions of power that are the hallmark of our country.  I was elected to go to D.C. to work for my constituents, to help our middle class, to help all our working families, and to create good paying jobs. I came to DC to make sure that all Americans, including new Americans, have the opportunity to work hard and achieve the American Dream. I am here to work with all who will work with me, to work across the aisle, irrespective of party affiliation.       I'm going to D.C. to be at the table when decisions are made that affect my constituents. Either we are at the table or we are on the menu.
Pleasure to be visited by Rickk Montoya and some of my great constituents. You're always welcome.

This Friday I will be hosting an Immigration Town Hall with speakers from U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services, the Orange County Hispanic Bar Association, the Consulmex Santa Ana and local immigration lawyers. This is a free event, and everyone is welcome.
Happy Birthday Congressman John Garamendi and Congressman Mike Thompson! Its great to share a birthday with you!
My staff surprised me for my birthday. Thanks all!
Photos from events
Photos of my Washington DC Office guests!
I am hosting an Immigration Town Hall in Phillips Hall Theatre at Santa Ana College at Santa Ana College. Know your rights. Watch it live now.
America must always welcome those that are prosecuted. Refugees from around the world look to us. We must not abandon them.

I went to LAX tonight to meet with the detainees and help with their release. I will continue to pursue this issue in Washington DC. This behavior goes against our American values and rights and cannot stand.

On Saturday, I went to LAX to help refugees. Today, I am announcing that I will introduce legislation to fund legal aid for immigrants, DREAMers, and refugees. President Trump’s Executive Orders directly challenges the right to due process guaranteed under our Constitution. My legislation will guarantee that DREAMers, immigrants, and refugees have the resources they need to fight for due process and breathe free.
Tuesday night is the deadline for ACA coverage! Don’t wait. Get covered. www.Healthcare.gov
Tonight I joined my fellow Democrats to stand up for immigrants and refugees looking towards us for help. We will not abandon you.
Real courage is doing what is right when you know you'll get fired. Good job Acting AG Yates.
Today, I was on FOX's Neil Cavuto discussing President Trump's executive order on immigration.
The passage of HR-612 is strong step to protecting our digital borders with one of our strongest allies, Israel. Together we can create the security necessary to protect our digital lives.
I'll be discussing my bill to fund legal services for immigrants, refugees and DREAMers on the floor today around noon! Tune it and watch.

Today I spoke on the Floor about the first bill I am introducing, the DREAMers, Immigrants, Refugees (DIRE) Legal Aid Act. This bill will provide legal aid to those targeted by President Trump's Executive Orders. They need our help. We can't abandon them.
Scapegoating immigrants is wrong. Today, I introduced my first bill, the DIRE Legal Aid Act, to provide legal services to the targets of President Trump's Executive Orders. We cannot abandon them.
Had the honor of hosting Ambassador Ramoón Gil-Casares from the Embassy of Spain in the United States. Thank you Sir!
I applaud the judge for upholding the law. We know the President's ban is unconstitutional. We must immediately correct the harm done to the affected families.

Bruno has always gone out of his way to help the homeless, the needy, kids, and anyone and everyone who needed a hand. He is our neighbor and our friend. Now in his time of need, let’s be there for him. Just as he has always been there for us.
Tuve la oportunidad de ser entrevistado por Juan Carlos Lopez de  CNN Directo USA sobre varios temas enfrentando a nuestras comunidades y nuestra nación. Oprima aquí para ver la entrevista.
I spoke with Secretary Kelly about immigration reform and how we can protect hardworking immigrants in the United States. Watch it here.
I met with with Jena Jensen from CHOC Children's Hospital about the millions of children who rely on Medicaid for their healthcare. Thanks, for stopping by Jena!
I won the #1 pick in the freshmen office lottery! See my office here.
The President's ban is unconstitutional. No matter how many times he appeals, it will remain unconstitutional. I applaud this judge for affirming we are a nation of inclusion.

I applaud Senator Kamala Harris for introducing her new bill. It goes hand in hand with H.R. 858, the DIRE Legal Aid Act. Together, our bills will guarantee due process and legal services for immigrants, refugees, and DREAMers.

I am greatly concerned by Thursday’s ICE Raids. Currently, we have more questions than answers and I urge restraint while we continue to investigate. My staff and I are working to ensure Due Process is protected. For now, know your rights.
Today I sent the following letter to ICE seeking answers to the raids in Southern California.
I am deeply concerned. Many of my constituents are scared. We need answers from ICE.
Director Homan failed to respond to my first letter, and cancelled today's meeting. We need answers about the Southern California ICE Raids.

I joined Congressman Luis V. Gutierrez and Congressional Hispanic Caucus to protest ICE’s refusal to meet with Latino leaders. Raids are happening in our neighborhoods, and ICE’s silence is making it harder to tell constituents not to be scared. ICE owes us answers, and I will fight until we get them.
I won’t stand for it. Kevin de León won't stand for it. Jerry Brown won't stand for it. If President Trump thinks he can use the California National Guard to round up families, he is sadly mistaken.

Neither the president of the United States nor his senior advisers in the White House seem to appreciate the important role of oversight in our nation’s system of checks and balances. Our Democracy is dependent on oversight and transparency.
On February 21, I will be hosting an Immigration Town Hall at Valley High School to address some of the issues our community faces. Please attend if you need immigration information or legal advice.

To me, drugs & keeping that poison away from our children is a top priority. I’ve been blessed that my family has avoided it, but many have not. Stopping the flow of illegal drugs into this country is a health issue, a national security issue, and a moral issue.

On February 23, I will be hosting an Immigration Town Hall at Santa Ana High School to address some of the issues our community faces. Please attend if you need immigration information or legal advice.
A happy ending to a scary event. Thank you, Officers.

On February 24, I will be hosting an Immigration Town Hall at the Rancho Santiago Community College District Building to address some of the issues our community faces. Please attend if you need immigration information or legal advice.
Tonight, I will be joined by Eliel Aguillon – a DACA recipient from Santa Ana, California, the first person in his family to attend college and an American in every sense of the word.
Let’s give DACA students — like my Presidential Address guest Eliel Aguillon — and other hard working taxpayers a pathway to citizenship. They are the new Americans.
DREAMers are Americans in every sense of the word. You are welcome in this country. You are welcome in my office.
Don't forget today is the deadline. Make sure to fill out your FASFA!
Daniela Vargas is facing deportation without a hearing. This is not American and is terrifying. Due process is for everyone.
The repeal bill does real harm to real people. Hard working Americans depend on ACA every day. We can’t go back.
There is no excuse for this. Taking children from their parents is cruel. Period.
When we ban immigrants, we ban doctors. 25% of our doctors were born somewhere else, but found education and opportunity in the United States. What could be more American than that?
I will not stand for millions of Californian losing their coverage. Obamacare works. The new plan doesn’t.
I’ve said it before, I’ll say it again. President Trump’s wall isn’t about security. It’s bad policy,  a bad idea, and a waste of money.
Photos of my Washington DC Office guests!

The numbers are in and they're worse than we imagined. The Repeal Bill rips coverage from 24 million Americans and kills medicaid as we know it.
President Trump can sign as many Executive Orders as he wants. His Muslim ban is unconstitutional. Period.
President Trump’s budget cuts our future. Science, job training, and our environment get axed.
Literal quote: Tucker Carlson: "The counties who voted for you will do far worse under your plan." President Trump: "Oh, I know..."

Reinstating the Spanish Whitehouse.gov is a matter of making government more transparent, more accountable, more effective for more people. At the end of the day it doesn't matter what language you speak, you're ultimately still a taxpayer and deserve access.
It is imperative we save the ACA. There is too much on the line.
I'll be offering my first Bill on the House Floor Today at 12:30et.
Today I sent this letter to the California State University Board of Trustees urging them not to raise tuition costs on half a millions of Californian students.
Undocumented Immigrants are our neighbors. Let's bring them out of the shadows. Providing a path to citizenship is the right thing to do.
If the AHCA comes to a vote, I'm voting no. We must protect the Affordable Care Act, and ensure it works for everyone!
My first bill just passed the House Floor 424 to 0!
We saved the ACA. Now its time to make it even better.
Are you a High School artist? Submit your work to the Congressional Art Competition for a chance to have your work displayed in the U.S. Capitol.
Sanctuary cities protect mothers and fathers. They need comprehensive immigration reform, not threats of losing funding.
Facebook has some great features to participate in local politics. Make sure to check out this new feature and stay involved!
Today I joined Nancy Pelosi, Democratic Whip Steny Hoyer, and Rep. Lucille Roybal-Allard for an immigration forum on the damage of separating families. We must protect immigrates and their families.
I've joined Nancy Pelosi, Rep. Lucille Roybal-Allard and my fellow House Democrats for an immigration forum on the damage indiscriminate enforcement does to families. Tune in and watch now.
Today we remember Cesar Chavez, a historic labor leader. He brought the rights of marginalized farm workers to the forefront and helped change our history. We will always remember his vision.
Stay involved. Make sure to subscribe to my newsletter!
Our mothers, daughters, & sisters deserve their fair share. Support stronger economies and stronger families by demanding equal pay. Tune in and watch.

Introduced a bill to require federal agency websites to be in English, Spanish, Chinese, Tagalog, and Vietnamese. My bill will  increase transparency and access to information for millions of Americans.

This jobs report shows we aren't headed in the right direction. I am working every day to create jobs and empower workers. We need a comprehensive plan to put Americans back to work and get people to the middle class.

We cannot tolerate Assad’s barbaric attack on his civilians. The US strike was an appropriate step to prevent Assad from using these weapons again, but I urge the White House not to send ground forces to Syria.
In case you missed it this Sunday, here is my profile from the Orange County Register
Visited by my good friend and California State University, Fullerton President Mildred Garcia. Wonderful to learn how my alma mater is shaping the leaders of tomorrow.
Wishing you and your family a Happy Easter!
Stay involved. Make sure to subscribe to my newsletter!
Remember! Taxes are due today. The Santa Ana Post Office - at 3101 W. Sunflower Ave - will be open until midnight tonight.
I'm saddened to learn a DREAMer was deported for forgetting his wallet. Let's do what’s right and give them legal status and end the targeting.
DHS admitted that Juan Manuel Montes's DACA status did not expire in 2015. He was protected and they still deported him. Let this DREAMer go home.
I'll be hosting an Citizenship Fair Saturday from noon to 5pm. If you are interested in becoming a U.S. citizen and want help filling out the application, join us at St. Matthews Church tomorrow.

Happening now: Join me at St. Matthews Church for my Citizenship Fair. We will be here to help you until 5pm.
Some photos of my Citizenship Fair. Thanks to everyone who came and volunteered! Still need information on becoming a citizen? Contact my office.
Congratulations Edmonton Oilers on making the playoffs for the first time since 2006, but I look forward to another Anaheim Ducks sweep in the second round! Let's go Ducks!

When the government shuts down, it slows our economy and make it harder for America to take care of those most in need. The last government shutdown cost our economy $24 billion. If we fail to pass a new budget, it is our veterans and seniors who will pay. We must not abandon the Americans we owe most.
1.5 million people died in the Armenian Genocide 102 years ago. It's time we acknowledge this atrocity and give the families the recognition they deserve.
Some good news for my friends and neighbors in Santa Ana, California . The courts continue to side with immigrants and the communities that support them.
Had a wonderful meeting with student scientist Ashley Le-Pham from California State University, Fullerton on the importance of student research and science funding.
Great to see my old friend Assemblymember Rocky Chávez!
Edie Falco and PETA (People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals) stopped by to talk about animal rights.
I met with the Sierra Club to discuss the importance of perserving open space and public parks. Thanks for stopping by!
Finally the truth. When ICE claimed to be deporting dangerous criminals they were actually deporting people for driving offenses or no record at all. No wonder they wouldn't meet with me.

Black April is a day of mourning and remembrance for the lives and freedom lost when #Saigon fell 42 years ago. Thousands escaped and made Orange County their home. Today we remember their sacrifices and the tragedies of the Vietnam War.

One big victory in the budget is year-round #PellGrant access for millions of students. As a Pell Grant recipient, I understand the value of investing in Affordable #College. I wouldn’t be here without it.
Immigrants are the backbone of our country. Today we stand in solidarity for their right to pursue the American dream. Watch it here.
I joined my colleagues and wore green today to bring awareness to Mental Health Awareness Month. Together we can end the stigma against mental illness and get people the help they need. #mhm2017

I spoke on the House Floor to commemorate Black April, and the sacrifices made in the search for freedom from tyranny. I am honored to represent this community and will continue to stand with them in defense of human rights and religious freedom.
Today I will be voting "NO" on the #AHCA. We must come together and make the Affordable Care Act works for every American!
Every May we celebrate the first person we ever knew, our mother. Today, let's take a moment to say thank you to the woman who gave us everything. Thank you, mom!
Another matter that President Trump and I agree on. We must bolster our nation’s cybersecurity, and address the growing threats to our networks.

Each year Americans come together to honor our Law Enforcement professionals, and mourn those who have given their lives in defense of their communities. These brave men and women have our back. We need to have theirs.
I'll be hosting a Town Hall and Immigration Workshop on May 30th. Make sure to RSVP so we can guarantee your questions get answered.
Join me for a Town Hall on May 30!
Our law enforcement working dogs are vital partners for the officers who protect our borders from terrorists and narco-traffickers. They keep Americans safe and help protect our national security.
Esta noche estaré en Telemundo para hablar sobre la agenda de deportación masiva de Trump y lo que estoy haciendo para detenerlo.
Estaré en la Perspectiva Nacional de Entravision organizada por Tsi-Tsi-Ki Félix el domingo 21 de mayo a las 4 PM. Sintonice para saber cómo la agenda del Presidente Trump le afecta.
Thank you California State Association of Letter Carriers (CSALC) for inviting me to speak at your 55th annual convention!
Harvey Milk built a movement. Today, his courage reminds us that no one can stop justice. When we fight for what is right, we will always win.
NA
A touching story about team work, love, and dedication. Congratulations Judy and Marty O’Connor on your accomplishment together!

Estuve en Perspectiva Nacional para discutir la agenda del presidente y asuntos con Rusia. Vea mi video con Tsitsiki Felix y aprenda cómo la agenda del presidente Trump le afecta a usted y a su familia.

There is no reason our veterans should ever wait up to 5 years to receive an answer to a benefit claim. That is unacceptable. That is why I strongly support H.R. 2288 - Veterans Appeals Improvement and Modernization Act of 2017. America owes these brave men and women swift and exceptional care for the wounds they suffered defending us. That is the least we can do.
Here at HITN talking with Gerson Borrero about issues important to me and my distinct.
Today marks the first day of Ramadan. To all our Muslim brothers and sisters fasting this month, I wish you a blessed Ramadan.
On Memorial Day we honor the brave men and women who gave their lives to build this nation.
I am honored to have taken part in the Anaheim Memorial Day Ceremony. Our veterans give us everything and we must never forget their sacrifices.

I get calls every week from concerned constituents. There is something wrong with our immigration system when people like Mr. Singh are denied the American dream. We must reform our immigration system and allow contributing members of society to follow their dreams.
I will be headed to Mexico with several of my colleagues to meet with deported veterans. If they're good enough to defend this country, they should be good enough to stay.

Last night at my Town Hall violence broke out when a group of Trump supporters attempted to shut down the event. I completely support the right of all parties to exercise their first amendment rights. However, I urge people to act responsibly and refrain from violence.

Last night a group of #Trump Supporters attempted to end our Town Hall. But after a heated exchange, and a little help from our local police officers, we ended up having a great event with some enthusiastic and interested constituents. Thanks everyone!

I am pleased to announce that Southern California Regional Rail Authority has been awarded a $3.2 million federal grant to implement Positive Train Control (PTC), which will save lives by preventing accidents like the tragic 2008 Chatsworth collision.

I will continue to hold Immigration Town Halls to educate constituents on the law and protecting their rights. Everyone deserves a chance at the American dream. Until we have comprehensive immigration reform, these communities will continue to live in fear.
I'll be on ABC7 Eyewitness News TODAY at 3 PM to discuss my trip to meet #DeportedVeterans in Mexico.
I was on ABC7 today with Elex Michaelson to talk about my trip to meet #DeportedVeterans in Mexico. These men and women served this country honorably. We must bring them home.
Our hearts go out to the victims and their families. While we don't know who is responsible for this latest attack, we must remain vigilant in the face of terror.
Here are some of the deported veterans. I had the honor to meet. Now it's time to get to work, and get them home.
Today I pledged to help deported veterans receive the respect they earned. No one who is honorably discharged should be dishonorably deported.
Our deported veterans served with honor. If you serve honorably, you should get your citizenship.
It is more important than ever that we protect contributing members of our society and keep families from being broken up. Comprehensive immigration reform is the only solution.
ABC7's Elex Michaelson joined me and my fellow Congressional Hispanic Caucus members to meet and share the stories of America's #DeportedVeterans.
Here in the United States, we never leave a solider behind.
Even after 73 years, the courage and bravery of the soldiers who participated in D-Day leaves me awestruck.

I'm excited to share the Irvine City Council has voted in favor of giving our Veterans a local resting place by building the Orange County Veterans Memorial Cemetery at "Strawberry Field" on the old El Toro Base.

After the Comey hearing it is even more apparent America must do more to defend against cyber attacks. This week I introduced a bill to strengthen our nation's offensive cyber security capabilities. World War 3 is raging right now in cyber space. With the increased frequency of cyber-attacks executed by foreign adversaries, we must increase our investments into securing our networks. My bill will help prevent the cyber espionage we saw during the past election. Protecting our networks is vital to the privacy and health of our democracy.

One year ago, a celebration of culture and community at Pulse Nightclub was shattered when 49 people were brutally murdered. Today, we pause to remember them, and acknowledge the pain of the survivors and families still steeped in heartbreak. But while we mourn, we must also stand up against the hate that allowed such a vile act to occur. Only together can we combat homophobia and help our LBGTQ+ family live with the dignity and peace they deserve.

One year ago, a celebration of culture and community at Pulse Nightclub was shattered when 49 people were brutally murdered. Today, we pause to remember them, and acknowledge the pain of the survivors and families still steeped in heartbreak. But while we mourn, we must also stand up against the hate that allowed such a vile act to occur. Only together can we combat homophobia and help our LBGTQ+ family live with the dignity and peace they deserve.
Joined by my good friends from AIPAC – The American Israel Public Affairs Committee.
Great to have Football back in Southern California! #LARams

#Russia breached 39 states during the 2016 election. I introduced my #cybersecurity bill to prevent this from ever happening again. It is vital to our democracy that we improve our offensive cyber capabilities to prevent every foreign power from ever being able to influence our elections again.

Fiscal responsibility begins with me. That’s why I make sure every penny of taxpayer money I spend is vital to my constituents and my work for the district. I am proud to be the lowest spending Freshmen Member in Congress.
I'll be on CNN en Español CNN Directo USA tonight to talk about cybersecurity and the threat of foreign interference.
The practice of deporting veterans is reprehensible. We must bring them home.
Our thoughts and prayers are with my colleagues, their staff, and our Capitol Police in this very difficult moment. We are all Americans and violence has no place in a democracy.

It is time to create a dedicated Smithsonian museum to commemorate the unique contributions #Latinos have made to the Untied States. From days of the Republic, Latinos have been there building the country we love.
DACA recipients are American in every sense expect for a piece of paper. Today marks the 5th anniversary of those protects becoming reality. We must continue to protect these young men and women.

Five years ago, #DACA was created to protect kids who are American in every sense expect for a piece of paper. These young people are as American as any of us. We must do everything we can to protect them and ensure they stay here in the only home they've ever known.
Tonight we celebrate unity and bipartisanship. #CongressionalBaseBallGame

It's quite symbolic that the Administration chose to rescind Deferred Action for Parents of Americans and Lawful Permanent Residents (“DAPA”) on the 5th Anniversary of  DACA. The President said that he would only go after criminals. Instead he has made it clear that honest, hard working, taxpaying moms and dads are targets. This will split more families apart and create further economic uncertainty for children. This is very sad day.
After months of fear and anxiety, DACA has been saved. They are Americans in every sense of the word, except for a piece of paper. Now we need to work to get them that paper.
Happy Father's Day Everyone!
Don't Forget! Tomorrow is my Office Grand Opening. Hope to see you there.
My deepest condolences to the families of the sailors lost in this tragic accident.
In 1983, Dr. Sally Ride became the first American Woman in space! A true trailblazer.  #WomenInStem
My heart goes out to Otto's family. What happened to him is appalling. The North Korean regime must be held accountable for their mistreatment of this young man.

Thank you everyone who came to my office grand opening last night! It was a pleasure to meet so many of my constituents and learn how I can better represent you in Washington. Stay tuned for future events!

I recognized these officers' courage and standout service in rescuing two young boys who were swept up in the Santa Ana River. Without concern for their own safety they saved lives. We are proud to have these men keeping our city safe.
I had a wonderful meeting with the Dalai Lama. He is an inspiration, and I am blessed to have had the opportunity to speak with him.
The United States must stand up for 65.6 million refugees looking towards America for hope. #WorldRefugeeDay
Summer has officially arrived in California. Stay cool everyone!
The suffering these refugees face is tragic. We must do all we can to help them find safety and one day return home. #WorldRefugeeDay
A true American Hero helping to make the world better. As a nation we should follow his example and do everything we can to help the refugees of this barbaric civil war.
NA
Happy first day of summer everyone!
Ensuring your taxes dollars are used correctly is one of my top priorities. Controlling our national debt starts with combating waste, fraud, and abuse.

We continue to find more and more evidence of the depth of Russia's involvement in our election. My bill demands the vulnerabilities be fixed and offensive capabilities developed to prevent this from ever happening again.
I was honored to join thousands of local Muslims as they gathered for the Eid prayer and the end of Ramadan.
I was honored to join in this year's Eid prayer. Eid Mubarak to all our Muslim friends and neighbors!
The Supreme Court just announced it would allowed the #travelban to take limited effect until it rules on President Trump's travel ban this fall.
The CBO announced 22 million Americans will lose Healthcare under Senate Bill.
22 million of America's most vulnerable citizens will lose healthcare under the new Senate bill.

Tonight I voted for a #bipartisan bill to help #veterans with specific skills get jobs after their service. This is just one of many bills we must pass to help our veterans. In my career, I have worked to pass numerous bills to help our veterans, including fast tracking security guard applications and combating veteran homelessness. I will continue to fight for our vets, just as they have fought for us.

Immigrants are a fundamental part of America. I sat down with the BBC to talk about how our failure to pass comprehensive immigration reform has prevented the United States from solving its immigration issues.

On Monday, my colleagues and I passed a bipartisan bill to help veterans get their commercial driver's license. I am happy to see the Senate has also taken up this cause. Together we can help our veterans here at home.

PTSD has become a household word but few people actually understand the invisible scars our warriors come home with. That is why it is so important for us to learn the signs to help those living through it. #PTSDAwarenessDay

After 9 years of leading the Orange County Sheriff's Department, Sandra Hutchens is retiring. Throughout her 40 year career, she has dedicated her life to keeping our families and communities safe.  Sandra Hutchens has earned my thanks and gratitude.

Tomorrow, Congress is voting on a law that would make Officer Jose Vargas, and thousands of immigrants just like him, felons by returning to the United States after being previously removed. Officer Vargas was everything a police officer should be, and his story is not only inspiring but quintessentially American. He achieved the American Dream, became a pillar of his community, and introduced a generation of Latinos in Orange County to a police officer they could trust. The United States is a better place because of him.

We honored Linda Yanez, this year's Congressional Art Contest winner. Some of you may recognize her art as the WWII mural from Barrio Logan in Santa Ana. I am overjoyed to share this part of our culture and community with my colleagues and our country through Linda's art.

HR 3004 dishonors heroes like Officer Jose Vargas, and Jose Angel Garibay, the first solder from Orange County killed in Iraq. Both of these men came to the United States as undocumented immigrants, and both made America a better place. We must keep bad hombres out, but we cannot brand millions of immigrants as criminals when their only crime is seeking a better life in America.

These two devastating anti-immigrant bills actually hurt our police officers’ ability to keep communities safe, demonize immigrants, and undermine the constitution. If you come to America with hatred in your heart and an intent to do harm, then there is no place for you in America. Sadly, these bills do not distinguish between felons and families whose only crime is being here undocumented, branding millions of hard working taxpayers as criminals.
I'm hosting a Summer Photo Contest! What makes your community great? Capture it and share it. Go to the event page for details on how to submit your work.

Hard working folks in our community and all across this country never fully recovered from the recession. These families are still struggling every day to get by and achieve the American Dream. It is our job in Congress to work together and help create the same kind of good paying jobs that my generation grew up on.
Our thoughts and prayers are with the plane's occupants. Stay safe everyone.

When immigrants are too afraid to come out of the shadows, this is what happens. All across America, farmers can't find workers to harvest their crops. Food is wasted, money is lost, and it's the local economies that pay the price. I've said it before, and I'll say it again, immigrants contribute to America. Give them green cards, bring them out of the shadows, and let's keep building our economy.

Drug detection dogs are one of our best and most cost effective tools we have to combat drug smugglers. That is why I'm working to get more canine teams deployed to our borders to combat drug smugglers. A multi-billion dollar wall won't stop vehicle smuggled narcotics, but canines and their handlers will.

On #IndependenceDay we celebrate the birth of our country, and acknowledge what it means to be free. So as we gather with our friends and families, let us take a moment to remember the sacrifices that created our nation. Together we will continue to make the United States the greatest country on Earth.
It is troubling to learn of North Korea’s latest bold claim. Regardless of the claims credibility, the world will not stand for North Korea’s provocations.

I am pleased the 9th circuit has decided to protect the children seeking asylum in the United States. We should be sheltering them, not detaining them and adding to their trauma. They are children and they need our help.

I'm happy our veterans will finally have a final resting place in Orange County. I have been strongly supportive of the creation of a local veteran memorial cemetery. Families should not have to drive a hundred miles to visit their loved ones. This is a good day for our vets.
A big welcome to my friend and colleague, Jimmy Gomez who will be joining us in Washington this week.
Summer is here and it's hot out there. Stay cool everyone!
This young man's quick thinking and courage saved lives. He is an example to his community.
California's economy is bigger and better than ever. As the 5th largest economy in the world, California's success proves it is possible to have good jobs, a clean environment, and a growing economy.

Last night both of my cybersecurity amendments passed the House. These amendments will give us the tools we need to keep our infrastructure, our networks, and our data safe from our adversaries. Increasing our protection from cyber-attacks is vital to our national security.
Back in June a group of veterans came to me concerned their legal use of medical marijuana would put their benefits at risk. I got a hold of the Secretary of the VA and found out the truth.

In the aftermath of the Vietnam War, 800,000 Vietnamese refugees fled persecution. They came with nothing, and rebuilt their lives in the United States. I am proud to honor their courage and strength.

California is projected to overtake the United Kingdom to become the 5th largest economy in the world. California's unemployment is at a 17-year low and its economic growth is nearly double the national average. Our economy continues to lead the U.S. and demonstrate what is possible.

Water District have been selected for WIFIA loans, which will allow for better more stable water supply in Orange County. Senator McCain has dedicated his entire life to the service of our nation. He is a war hero and a patriot whose integrity and honesty has made him the model of a statesman. I wish him and his family strength through this difficult time, and pray for his recovery.

When I was young the fear was nuclear war. Now, a small piece of malicious software can bring down a power grid. Investing in cybersecurity is a matter of national security. We must invest in programs that can create the next generation of cyber warriors. If we don’t invest in these programs now, we will never catch up. It is also a way for us to help our students prepare for the jobs of the future by getting more kids interested in STEM fields. The Defense partnerships with the aerospace industry defined the 20th century. Cybersecurity partnerships will define the century. Together we can keep our nation safe and create good jobs for our children in the progress.
I am proud of my Senate colleagues for introducing the #DREAMAct and standing up for #DREAMers. This bipartisan bill will give DREAMers the protection and peace of mind they deserve.
I'll be hosting a Town Hall on veterans issues on August 21. Learn about the new GI Bill, changes at Veterans Affairs, and how I am fighting for Veterans.
I was so honored to speak with Korean-American students from across California who came to Washington DC to advocate for their communities. These young American give me hope for our nation's future.

Police chiefs from across the country agree, sanctuary cities keep our communities safe. Punishing sanctuary cities makes it harder for Police chiefs to prosecute hardened violent criminals. If you want to end sanctuary cities, end the policies that force hardworking taxpayers to live in the shadows. Comprehensive immigration reform is the only real solution.

There are many effective ways to protect our borders. A $1.6 billion wall isn't one of them. On the House Homeland Security Committee I have worked and passed legislation that would give our security professionals the tools they need to stop smugglers and narcoterrorists. Tools like drug sniffing k-9s and a well funded Coast Guard stop drug smugglers and make us safer. Billion dollar walls don't.
An estimated 150,000 transgender Americans have served our country. This change in policy dishonors their service and their sacrifice.

There are many effective ways to protect our borders, but a $1.6 billion wall isn't one of them. I have passed legislation that invests in drug sniffing canine, smart technology at our borders crossings, and our Coast Guard to stop drug smugglers and narcoterrorists from entering our country. These programs need our support, not an ineffective wall.

Joel Colindres is just the latest example of how our immigration policies fail people. This young man fled violence in Guatemala more than a decade ago and has built a life in the United States. When Joel is deported, a hardworking, taxpaying, home-owning father will be deported. We must reform our immigration system.

I cosponsored an amendment that will provide scholarships to America's next generation of cyber warriors. These scholarships will allow us to train new cybersecurity experts, helping keep our nation safe and provide good paying jobs to our children.

The Statue of Liberty stands for #inclusion, #acceptance, and #freedom. The young woman who painted this is trying very hard to show people that she is an #American. If I took down her painting, I’d be telling the world her experiences don’t matter and she did something wrong. This is her country too, and she earned that spot on my wall.

"As we continue to #evolve as a nation, Lady Liberty evolves with us." Our commitment to #diversity, #inclusion, and #freedom continues to make the #UnitedStates the greatest nation on earth. It's about time the symbols of our liberty caught up.
Congratulations Chapman University on your grant to research Breast Cancer Treatment!

We are all Americans. We all love this country regardless of our religion, ethnicity, or place of origin. We get to choose what being an American means for ourselves, and that freedom is what makes this country so great.
There is no place for bigotry in the United States.
I'll be asking Homeland Security Committee to conduct hearings to investigate white supremacist domestic terrorism and how we can prevent it.

Our country has a homegrown #terrorism problem we refuse to address. That ends now. We must hold hearings and finally address that terrorism inflicted by white supremacy extremists is destroying our country.
Today I sent a letter requesting a formal hearing on the dangers posed by white supremacist. We must address the dangers posed by the white supremacy movement.

When #DACA was created, 800,000 #DREAMers came our of the shadows, registered, underwent a background check, and routinely renewed their status. They didn’t want to hide. The United States is their home, and they are proud to be a part of it.   Today, on the fifth anniversary of DACA, their future is under imminent threat. DREAMers need legislative protection now. I urge my colleagues to join me to protect DREAMers. This is the only home they have ever known. They deserve to stay.

Chairman McCaul responded to my letter requesting a hearing on the rise of #WhiteSupremacist domestic #terrorism. I hope the hearing on September 12 will be dedicated to this homegrown terrorist threat.
My heart goes out to the victims of today's barbaric attack in Spain. We will not allow terror to break our spirit or strength.

The strength of our economy and our position as a world leader depends on our immigration system. Over the next 30 years, the United States will need substantial economic growth to meet our obligations to retiring baby boomers. If we are going to have an economy capable of honoring our promises, we need immigrants of all skill levels.
I urge everyone who will be standing up against #hate on Sunday to be safe and nonviolent. We must stand up for what is right and stand against hate in our communities.

Don't forget tonight is my Veterans Town Hall. Join me and my panel of experts to learn about the benefits available to veterans and how I am helping veterans attend college and get better healthcare.
Tonight I'm hosting a Veterans Town Hall to help our local heroes learn how to get the benefits they earned. If you're a veteran and need help with your benefits contact my office and get help.
As Hurricane Harvey heads towards Texas, I hope everyone stays safe.
A needless action that hurts our military, degrades our values, and discriminates against patriots.

President Trump has made it known he will likely end #DACA. This is unconscionable. We must protect hardworking #DREAMers who are already contributing to our communities. The expulsion of these young people would be #immoral and unforgivable. This is the only home they have ever known. They deserve to stay.

I am deeply saddened at this devastating policy change. These children are Americans in every sense of the word. We owe it to them and our country to ensure that they can stay here. This is a sad day for America.
Today is a dark day in America. The only crime DACA students are guilty of is aspiring for the American Dream.
They are good, lively kids and right now they are scared to death.

For many veterans, medical marijuana is the most effective tool for treating PTSD. Our veterans have served our country. They are heroes. If medical marijuana brings them relief, then we should give it to them.

The only crime DACA students are guilty of is aspiring for the American Dream. They have studied and worked hard to become contributing parts of their communities and our country. Even our private sector leaders support them.  We must keep fighting and keep hope alive. I hope the President will not go after children, and will reconsider his decision. The President needs to consider the lives he will destroy and the economic damage he will inflict if DREAMers are not protected. They are Americans in every sense of the word.
We must protect DREAMers. They're Americans in every sense of the word. They deserve to stay in the only home they have ever known.
These kids are model citizens. They follow the law. They study and work hard. They deserve our protection.
This is what we know.
Esto es lo que sabemos.
Sadly, for 16 years there has been legislation to protect DREAMers but no action. Its time to bring these bills to the floor.

#DREAMers are American in every sense of the word. They are a vital part of our communities and economy. We will not rest until legislation is passed that gives them the protections they need and deserve.
I'll be on Perspectiva Nacional with Congressman Luis V. Gutierrez this Sunday to talk about #DACA and what the House is doing to protect #DREAMers.
If you are a #DACA recipient and need help, you can make a confidential meeting with our caseworkers. Call 714-559-6190.

I joined Congressman Luis V. Gutierrez and Congressman Raul M. Grijalva and a group of DREAMers for a press conference today. We will defend our #DREAMers and we will get them the legislative protection they need.

Sixteen years ago our country changed forever. The tragedy and sorrow of September 11th is etched in our souls. We honor those who lost their lives that day, and — today and tomorrow — will be vigilant and ready to protect our country from those that would do us harm. We will never forget.

Since the Vietnam War, Vietnamese immigrants have moved to Orange County to be with family and escape the oppression they face at home. If you're on the fence about how #DREAMers contribute to our society, read this article. The The Cato Institute, a conservative think-tank, disproves some of the most prevalent myths about #DACA. DREAMers don't take jobs from Americans, cost taxpayers money, or make their communities unsafe. They make American great, and we can prove it.

There has been much talk from a lot of well intentioned individuals, but it is time to walk the walk and start delivering real legislative relief to our DREAMers. Countless business leaders, including Facebook’s Founder Mark Zuckerberg and Apple CEO Tim Cook, as as well as 90% of Americans and 76% of Republicans believe these hardworking young people should have a pathway to citizenship. It is time for the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs to do a clinical study on using #MedicalMarijuana to treat #ChronicPain in veterans and help stop the #OpioidCrisis. Opioid prescriptions for veterans have increased by 270% since 2003, resulting in 68,000 veterans developing an opioid addiction, and a two-fold increase accidental opioid overdose deaths. This is unacceptable.   It is imperative to the health and safety of our #veterans that we find alternative treatments for their chronic pain. Veterans want medical marijuana and I am willing to try anything that will bring these brave men and women the relief they deserve.
I participated in a legislative roundtable to talk about the importance of investing in healthcare and infrastructure. Watch it here.

I spoke with students from Katella High School about the importance of a good education and going to college. These young students are participating in GEAR Up a #college prep program that helps students learn the skills they’ll need to succeed in their #education.

Today we broke ground for Orange County’s only veteran’s cemetery. I am very happy our Veterans finally have a resting place in Orange County. #OrangeCounty has the fourth largest population of #Veterans in California. After a lifetime of service, the 130,000 Veterans in Orange County deserve a final resting place close to their family and the communities they enriched. This #cemetery will finally let Veterans rest in dignity close to home.

I am proud my colleagues in the Senate joined in helping our fellow Americans. The unimaginable devastation done by the #CaliforniaFires and the #hurricanes in Puerto Rico, Florida, and the Virgin Islands, makes it is imperative we come together and help those Americans who have lost everything.

I was on CNN Directo USA to talk about our #Veteran  #OpioidCrisis. Opioid prescriptions for veterans have increased 270% since 2003 resulting in 68,000 veterans developing opioid addictions. This is unacceptable. It is imperative to the health and safety of our #veterans that we find alternative treatments for their #ChronicPain including #MedicalMarijuana.

There is no better example of how broken our immigration system is than this. At its core, immigration is about people. And when the system fails people, this is what happens. We need #ComprehensiveImmigrationReform.

Chairman Michael McCaul joined me at John Wayne Airport, Orange County to learn about the unique #security issues facing #OrangeCounty. I'm glad the Chairman was able to learn about some of the issues we can fix together in the Homeland Security Committee, and look forward to getting to #work.

I'm touring the Port of Los Angeles with Homeland Security Committee Chairman Michael McCaul and Congressman Bennie G. Thompson. The Port of Los Angeles is the largest port in the United States and generates over $1.2 billions daily. Ensuring it is safe and secure is vital to our economy and getting the goods we need from around the world.
You can watch Homeland Security Committee's field hearing at the Port of Los Angeles here. I'm here learning how we can protect #USA's largest seaport.
Heartbreaking news from New York City. We will be watching this incident develop. My thoughts and prayers are with all affected.

The United States will always stand firm against those who would wish us harm. We will continue to be vigilant to defend our country and fellow Americans. We will find those responsible and bring them to justice. Acts of terror will never break us. My thoughts and prayers are with the families of today’s attack.
I am proud of these  Santa Ana High School #NJROTC students. They are the future of our nation's defense.
Thank you to everyone who came to my Town Hall. I'm always here to help you better understand your #government and how my work in Washington helps you. I'm here for you.

This year at the Orange Field of Valor, 1,776 flags were proudly flown, each honoring a friend or family member's service to our nation. Thank you The CFO for this beautiful tribute to our #Veterans and Active Duty soldiers.

At this week's #YoungCongressionalLeaders seminar students from around the district got a chance to meet their local elected leaders and learn how each branch of government works for them. The U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs thanked me for my work on the House Committee on Veterans' Affairs and presented me with a pin commemorating #VeteransDay. Ensuring our Nation's brave men and women get everything they earned is some of the most important work of my life. I am humbled by their courage, and honored to serve them.

Our country makes a promise to every person who puts on a uniform. You stand for us, and we’ll stand with you. We must ensure every #veteran gets the respect and benefits they earned. Their mission was to protect us. It's our mission to protect them.

I couldn't agree with Secertary Gates more. "Being an American is more than just passing an exam about United States history and the Constitution... Being an American is also about a willingness to put oneself in harm’s way to defend the country. It is about honor and duty."

In honor of Veterans’ Day I introduced two Veterans’ bills to help our heroes. #Veterans represent the best of America. In return for their sacrifices, this country promises every solider that we’ll have their back. Their mission was protecting us. Now that they’re home, it is our mission to protect them.

All gave some and some made the ultimate sacrifice. Today, let's pause to honor the courage and sacrifice of our #Veterans. As we observe this day, we give our heartfelt thanks to those who risk their lives to protect us.  As a member of the House Committee on Veterans' Affairs, I'm proud to report we continue to work hard to keep our promises to all of our Veterans. We set our differences aside, and do what is right for our Veterans.   To our Veterans, I am humbled by your courage and forever in your debt. Thank you for your service.

#Veterans represent the best of America. This country promises every soldier that we’ll have their back. Their mission was protecting us. Now that they’re home, it is our mission to protect them. That’s why I’ve introduced two bills to do just that.
If you’re in Washington, District of Columbia the Veterans History Project is at the The Library of Congress. This project interviews thousands of #veterans to preserve their stories. Check it out.
#Veterans living with chronic pain want #medical #marijuana. If it brings them relief, we need to give it to them.
Today I joined #Veterans from around the county in commemorating their service. Honored to spend time with these heroes.

Ending chronic pain and the daily suffering of our veterans should be every Member of Congress’s first priority. #MedicalMarijuana can be the answer. I’m here talking about answers with Congressman Matt Gaetz Congressman Tom Garrett NFL player Kyle Turley, and Veterans Cannabis Project founder Navy SEAL Nick Etten. Watch the press conference here.

#MedicalMarijuana offers real answers to people suffering from chronic pain. For our #Veterans, this can be the answer they need. Yesterday, I joined my colleagues to welcome former #NFL player Kyle Turley to share his story on how medical marijuana helped him recover from years of concussions and got him off dangerous #opioids. Kyle’s story is reflective of what countless veterans tell me. MedicalMarijuana gave them their lives back.

Today, I visited Ronald Reagan Washington National Airport with my colleagues from the Homeland Security Committee to see firsthand how the Transportation Security Administration keeps travelers secure in the air.

Latest "New From Lou, " is up. Check it out to see highlights of my week in DC.

Immediately after the attack in Charlotteville, I called for a hearing in the Homeland Security Committee on the threats posed by white supremacists. It never happened. I hope the House Judiciary Committee will hold one now. We need action.
Had the honor of recognizing Kieu Chinh and the 60th anniversary of Kieu-Chinh Cinema. She’s a treasured part of our community.
From my family to yours, Happy #Thanksgiving.
Today is Small Business Saturday! Small businesses are the backbone of our economy. Support your community and local economy by shopping local and #ShoppingSmall.

A lost life is a lost life. Every American lost to any terror attack, whether domestic or international, is a national tragedy. We need to prioritize all threats to ensure the safety of all Americans.
America lost a hero. Rest in peace Colonel.

Today, I hosted another session of the Young Congressional Leaders program, where #students from around the district got the opportunity to learn from WWII #veterans. These vets shared what it was like to fight for their country in a global war. I am honored they could join us and show today’s students what it took to be the #greatest generation.

I introduced the DIRE Legal Aid Act when the Travel Ban was first introduced to give those trapped in our legal system hope. The Supreme Court’s decision to uphold President Trump’s travel ban reinforces why my bill is so important. When we allow fear to dictate our national security, we abandon our moral standing and turn our back to the world.

More and more reports are showing the damage the new tax bill will have on #California. The Orange County Register has reported the bill will hurt retirees and make it harder for Orange County to build more affordable housing. Orange County deserves real solutions. This isn't one.

Although I am not a supporter of many of President Trump’s policies, I do not support impeaching President Trump at this time. Any discussion of impeachment before the completion of Robert Mueller’s investigation is premature and not in the best interest of our nation.

I am a strong supporter of Israel and the U.S.-Israel relationship. However, in the interest of #peace, I currently do not support moving the US Embassy to Jerusalem. The Clinton, Bush, and Obama Administrations all delayed the moving of the US Embassy. I believe in continuing that policy.

In #California, our law enforcement decides who gets issued a concealed carry permit. We require these permits because guns aren’t toys and carrying one in public without proper training can be deadly. This bill will allow people who don’t meet California’s standards to carry a concealed weapon in our streets. Our #police officers oppose this legislation. I voted with our public safety officers and to keep our streets #safe.
The Congressional Budget Office has new numbers on how the tax bill will affect Americans, and they aren't good for the middle class.

I am saddened to learn of the passing of Bishop Dominic Luong, the first native-born Vietnamese Roman Catholic Bishop in the United States. Bishop Luong dedicated his life to serving refugee and immigrant communities nationwide and was invaluable in helping Vietnamese refugees acclimate to the United States. His service will always be remembered.

I had the wonderful opportunity to send a few holiday cards to our servicemembers overseas. These brave men and women sacrifice so much for us. In this time of giving, the least we can do is say thank you.

As a long supporter of net neutrality and the internet, I am disappointed that the #FCC has undone current #NetNeutrality protections. It is clear that Americans from all walks of life want enforceable protections in place to ensure an open internet for everyone. Unfortunately, when Congress refuses to legislate and instead passes the buck to the FCC, the stability, and openness of the internet will depend on the whims of the White House.   Congress must #act to protect access to broadband for every #American, and ensure all of our constituents can access the internet without the threat of throttling or blackouts.

In November I voted ‘#NO’ on the tax bill because it was bad for California. Today, I voted ‘NO’ for the same reason. #California is already a donor state to the federal government. This tax bill only makes it worse.  Californians need tax reform. As the fifth largest economy in the world, Californians need federal tax policy that creates jobs, empowers our local businesses, helps California, and helps Main Street. Unfortunately, this bill doesn’t do that.  This bill forces #hardworking Californians to pay more to offset expensive tax cuts for America’s most well off. According to the nonpartisan Tax Policy Centers, 86 million households will see their taxes increase, with 83% of the tax cuts going to the top 1%.  As a Congressman, I need to support legislation that helps our neighbors, our working families, and our #smallbusinesses here in California. This bill doesn’t do that.
